ing, but now have a question.<br>
<br>
I choose SB for other reasons than 2 handers, but from reading this board, it sounds like I should be using one?  I'm only 10th, so maybe things change, but my Bastard Sword and Left Axe seem to work better.  My Build?  Approximately:<br>
<br>
6 LA<br>
7 Sword<br>
7 CA<br>
3 Stealth (auto-trained)<br>
<br>
Am I doing something wrong?  Do 2 handers only work better if you DON'T train LA?  Or do they only help with higher level styles?  What's the deal?  I don't want to miss out on what may be an advantage in an already difficult-enough class.<br>
<br>
Oh, and while I'm asking questions... I was planning on going completely without envenom.  It doesn't sound that great, and I personally don't like messing with &quot;Ammunition&quot; (I'd NEVER play an archer), or having to reapply poisons between every fight.  If I have any ability, I want to be able to use it.  Anyway, am I really gimping myself, or will I be ok if I can last without Envenom until a certain level?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for your answers,<br>
<br>
Eiger<br>
Shadowblade, Nimue <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaxterixenobelix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Axterix EnObelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 5:43:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two-Handed Weapon Benefit?</span><hr size=1> You don't need envenom.<br>
<br>
2h provides a higher base damage for opening CS styles (the bonus remains the same) and has a higher cap (due to being slower and 2h's 30% cap bonus).  To optimally take advantage of that front loaded damage, you'd want very high weapon and CS spec.<br>
<br>
At low levels, you're really best off focusing on 2 skills.  Either weapon + CS with 2h backstabs or else weapon + left axe with left axe styles.  You can dabble a bit in a 3rd skill, but focusing on keeping 2 near level will help you the most in early PvE.  Eventually, you'll want to up stealth more than just letting it auto-train, but early on, it works fine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ueigerdaoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiger DAOC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/12/02 5:53:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Two-Handed Weapon Benefit?</span><hr size=1> Ahh, great, thank you for the helpful reply.<br>
<br>
Ok, so the 2-Hander only helps with Damage CAP, that makes sense.  And I haven't seen a difference, because I'm not near the cap.<br>
<br>
And yes, as well as going with no Envenom, I had planned to give LA a rest for a while, now that I've got the Ravager Style.<br>
<br>
Thanks again,<br>
<br>
Eiger<br>
<br>
